# PHP Environment Requirements

## Required PHP Version
- PHP 8.3.x (API version 20230831)
- ZTS (Thread Safe) build required
- Visual C++ 2019 x64 runtime

## Required PHP Extensions
- fileinfo
- gd
- intl
- mbstring
- mysqli
- openssl
- pdo_mysql
- pdo_sqlite
- xsl
- zip
- redis

## Environment Configuration
- PHP modules must match the PHP API version (20230831)
- Extensions should be loaded from the correct path (C:/laragon/bin/php/php-8.3.16-Win32-vs16-x64/ext)
- Session save path should be configured to C:/laragon/tmp

## Testing Requirements
- PHPUnit must be installed via Composer
- All required extensions must be enabled before running tests
- MySQL and Redis services must be running and accessible
- Test environment should use separate database and Redis instances

## Common Issues
1. Module API Version Mismatch
   - Ensure PHP and modules are compiled with the same API version
   - Check module paths in php.ini
   - Verify extension loading order

2. Missing Extensions
   - Verify extension files exist in the ext directory
   - Check extension= lines in php.ini
   - Ensure DLL dependencies are available

3. Service Connections
   - Verify MySQL service is running
   - Check Redis service status
   - Validate connection credentials

## Testing Workflow
1. Verify PHP environment
2. Check required extensions
3. Start required services
4. Run test suite
5. Review test results
6. Address any failures
7. Record successful test run
